<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Cardiff City have dramatically sacked star winger Nathanial Mendez-Laing. </p>

<p>The Championship club revealed on Wednesday afternoon that the player's contract had been terminated with immediate effect but the reason for his dismissal is yet to be disclosed. </p>

<p>A club statement read: 'Cardiff City Football Club has, with immediate effect, terminated the contract of Nathaniel Mendez-Laing.</p>

<p>'The club will not be making any further comment on the matter.'</p>

<p>The player deleted all of his social media channels as speculation gathered pace as to the reason behind his breach of contract, which in turn led to his sacking. </p>

<p>Manager Neil Harris had revealed previously that the player was not involved in pre-season because of 'personal reasons'. </p>

<p>More to follow.  </p>
